00:22:54,367 --> 00:22:56,786
[sighs] 'Sup, amigo?

504
00:22:59,372 --> 00:23:01,166
Yeah, it ain't gettin' better.

505
00:23:01,249 --> 00:23:03,543
Hey, Heather, your
little boyfriend's here.

506
00:23:07,547 --> 00:23:09,091
You two don't stay out too late now.

507
00:23:09,174 --> 00:23:11,634
Come on, babe, Shark
Tank is about to start.

508
00:23:16,973 --> 00:23:18,057
You got a minute?

509
00:23:19,517 --> 00:23:20,768
[sighs] You know what?

510
00:23:20,852 --> 00:23:23,563
I'm done. Sound familiar?

511
00:23:24,397 --> 00:23:25,565
It does.

512
00:23:29,902 --> 00:23:31,446
Maggie, you annoy me.

513
00:23:33,865 --> 00:23:35,074
Aw, thank you.

514
00:23:35,158 --> 00:23:36,618
Other men bring flowers.

515
00:23:38,911 --> 00:23:40,788
And I know that I annoy you.

516
00:23:41,998 --> 00:23:43,895
But if this is gonna work, we're both

517
00:23:43,921 --> 00:23:45,817
gonna have to put up with some stuff.

518
00:23:46,419 --> 00:23:47,420
All right.

519
00:23:48,463 --> 00:23:50,215
I'm sorry about walking out...

520
00:23:51,007 --> 00:23:53,260
when you brought up Brenda.

521
00:23:53,343 --> 00:23:54,761
What do you want me to say?

522
00:23:55,595 --> 00:23:56,638
I was lost.

523
00:23:58,055 --> 00:23:59,724
You'd just moved out.

524
00:23:59,807 --> 00:24:02,477
I needed to get a haircut. She cut hair.

525
00:24:05,021 --> 00:24:06,689
I was upset over you.

526
00:24:07,649 --> 00:24:09,359
Her husband had just passed.

527
00:24:09,442 --> 00:24:10,818
We talked.

528
00:24:11,944 --> 00:24:13,070
That's it.

529
00:24:13,946 --> 00:24:15,657
I know all that.

530
00:24:15,740 --> 00:24:17,825
I brought up Brenda to prove a point.

531
00:24:17,909 --> 00:24:21,246
When things get
uncomfortable, you shut down.

532
00:24:21,329 --> 00:24:24,123
And I'm afraid if I move
back into that house...

533
00:24:24,207 --> 00:24:26,584
we're gonna go back to the
way we were before I left.

534
00:24:28,795 --> 00:24:30,588
I'm not saying things
are gonna be perfect.

535
00:24:30,672 --> 00:24:33,090
Oh, that was clear when
you told me I annoy you.

536
00:24:35,760 --> 00:24:38,638
I'm a different person
than I was 15 years ago.

537
00:24:38,721 --> 00:24:41,641
And I don't wanna go back
to the way it was, either.

538
00:24:41,724 --> 00:24:44,227
Oh... glad to hear that.

539
00:24:47,021 --> 00:24:48,606
I don't wanna lose you, Mags.

540
00:24:50,358 --> 00:24:52,652
You know, in your whole
life, you only get...

541
00:24:52,735 --> 00:24:55,655
one person who knows you best.

542
00:24:56,864 --> 00:24:58,325
And that's you.

543
00:24:58,408 --> 00:25:00,910
[sighs] Damn it, Beau.

544
00:25:01,869 --> 00:25:04,205
When did you learn to
say all the right things?

545
00:25:05,873 --> 00:25:07,875
I saw The Bridges of Madison County.

546
00:25:14,716 --> 00:25:16,133
I think your mom is awesome.

547
00:25:16,218 --> 00:25:18,887
It's just that Rooster's... not.

548
00:25:18,970 --> 00:25:22,390
I don't want what's going
on with them to screw us up.

549
00:25:23,099 --> 00:25:24,934
Fine, say they do break up.

550
00:25:25,017 --> 00:25:26,686
Yeah, let's pray they break up.

551
00:25:26,769 --> 00:25:29,314
[chuckles] No, who cares?

552
00:25:29,397 --> 00:25:31,816
They got their thing and we got ours.

553
00:25:32,567 --> 00:25:33,610
I like you.

554
00:25:34,402 --> 00:25:37,822
Nothing's changin'
that, no matter what they do.

555
00:25:37,905 --> 00:25:39,907
Give me a second.

556
00:25:39,991 --> 00:25:42,577
Dear Lord, break 'em up.

557
00:25:42,660 --> 00:25:44,537
Go, Broncos. Amen.

558
00:25:44,621 --> 00:25:45,747
[Heather chuckles]

559
00:25:45,830 --> 00:25:48,666
[sighs] Look, if you're okay
with this, I won't worry.

560
00:25:48,750 --> 00:25:50,668
I might still kick my brother's ass...

561
00:25:50,752 --> 00:25:52,545
- [chuckles]
- but we'll be fine.

562
00:25:53,380 --> 00:25:55,715
- High school phenom, Colt Bennett.
- Oh, yeah.

563
00:25:55,798 --> 00:25:56,883
Your table's ready.

564
00:25:58,426 --> 00:26:00,094
